{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":567,"text":"Well, now we're going to the Bahamas to meet"},{"time":2844,"text":"a remarkable group of dolphins that I've been working with"},{"time":5087,"text":"in the wild for the last 28 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":8554,"text":"Now I'm interested in dolphins because of their large brains"},{"time":11749,"text":"and what they might be doing with all that brainpower"},{"time":13863,"text":"in the wild."},{"time":15338,"text":"And we know they use some of that brainpower"},{"time":17610,"text":"for just living complicated lives,"},{"time":19774,"text":"but what do we really know about dolphin intelligence?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":22634,"text":"Well, we know a few things."},{"time":24338,"text":"We know that their brain-to-body ratio,"},{"time":26527,"text":"which is a physical measure of intelligence,"},{"time":28497,"text":"is second only to humans."},{"time":30993,"text":"Cognitively, they can understand"},{"time":32551,"text":"artificially-created languages."},{"time":34980,"text":"And they pass self-awareness tests in mirrors."},{"time":38121,"text":"And in some parts of the world, they use tools,"},{"time":40225,"text":"like sponges to hunt fish."},{"time":42540,"text":"But there's one big question left:"},{"time":45191,"text":"do they have a language, and if so,"},{"time":47058,"text":"what are they talking about?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":49462,"text":"So decades ago, not years ago,"},{"time":52905,"text":"I set out to find a place in the world"},{"time":55068,"text":"where I could observe dolphins underwater"},{"time":56866,"text":"to try to crack the code of their communication system."},{"time":60109,"text":"Now in most parts of the world, the water's pretty murky,"},{"time":62723,"text":"so it's very hard to observe animals underwater,"},{"time":65962,"text":"but I found a community of dolphins that live"},{"time":67721,"text":"in these beautiful, clear, shallow sandbanks of the Bahamas"},{"time":70747,"text":"which are just east of Florida."},{"time":72989,"text":"And they spend their daytime resting and socializing"},{"time":75400,"text":"in the safety of the shallows, but at night,"},{"time":77270,"text":"they go off the edge and hunt in deep water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81069,"text":"Now, it's not a bad place to be a researcher, either."},{"time":84893,"text":"So we go out for about five months every summer"},{"time":87069,"text":"in a 20-meter catamaran, and we live, sleep and work"},{"time":91271,"text":"at sea for weeks at a time."},{"time":93349,"text":"My main tool is an underwater video with a hydrophone,"},{"time":95989,"text":"which is an underwater microphone, and this is so"},{"time":97939,"text":"I can correlate sound and behavior."},{"time":100033,"text":"And most of our work's pretty non-invasive."},{"time":101679,"text":"We try to follow dolphin etiquette while we're in the water,"},{"time":104501,"text":"since we're actually observing them physically in the water."},{"time":107629,"text":"Now, Atlantic spotted dolphins are a really nice species"},{"time":110769,"text":"to work with for a couple of reasons."},{"time":112733,"text":"They're born without spots, and they get spots with age,"},{"time":115664,"text":"and they go through pretty distinct developmental phases,"},{"time":118698,"text":"so that's fun to track their behavior."},{"time":120640,"text":"And by about the age of 15, they're fully spotted black and white."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124093,"text":"Now the mother you see here is Mugsy."},{"time":126516,"text":"She's 35 years old in this shot,"},{"time":128501,"text":"but dolphins can actually live into their early 50s."},{"time":131691,"text":"And like all the dolphins in our community,"},{"time":134994,"text":"we photographed Mugsy and tracked her little spots"},{"time":137765,"text":"and nicks in her dorsal fin,"},{"time":139507,"text":"and also the unique spot patterns"},{"time":141710,"text":"as she matured over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144053,"text":"Now, young dolphins learn a lot as they're growing up,"},{"time":146712,"text":"and they use their teenage years to practice social skills,"},{"time":149787,"text":"and at about the age of nine, the females"},{"time":152140,"text":"become sexually mature, so they can get pregnant,"},{"time":154810,"text":"and the males mature quite a bit later,"},{"time":156781,"text":"at around 15 years of age."},{"time":158896,"text":"And dolphins are very promiscuous,"},{"time":160636,"text":"and so we have to determine who the fathers are,"},{"time":163498,"text":"so we do paternity tests by collecting fecal material"},{"time":165952,"text":"out of the water and extracting DNA."},{"time":168816,"text":"So what that means is, after 28 years,"},{"time":171280,"text":"we are tracking three generations,"},{"time":173688,"text":"including grandmothers and grandfathers."},{"time":176032,"text":"Now, dolphins are natural acousticians."},{"time":178648,"text":"They make sounds 10 times as high"},{"time":180932,"text":"and hear sounds 10 times as high as we do."},{"time":183120,"text":"But they have other communication signals they use."},{"time":185715,"text":"They have good vision, so they use body postures to communicate."},{"time":189056,"text":"They have taste, not smell."},{"time":191256,"text":"And they have touch."},{"time":193296,"text":"And sound can actually be felt in the water,"},{"time":195492,"text":"because the acoustic impedance of tissue and water's about the same."},{"time":198523,"text":"So dolphins can buzz and tickle each other at a distance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202153,"text":"Now, we do know some things about how sounds are used"},{"time":204693,"text":"with certain behaviors."},{"time":206102,"text":"Now, the signature whistle is a whistle"},{"time":208201,"text":"that's specific to an individual dolphin, and it's like a name. (Dolphin whistling noises)"},{"time":212900,"text":"And this is the best-studied sound,"},{"time":215076,"text":"because it's easy to measure, really,"},{"time":216705,"text":"and you'd find this whistle when mothers and calves"},{"time":218662,"text":"are reuniting, for example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220799,"text":"Another well studied sound are echolocation clicks."},{"time":223857,"text":"This is the dolphin's sonar. (Dolphin echolocation noises)"},{"time":227103,"text":"And they use these clicks to hunt and feed."},{"time":230420,"text":"But they can also tightly pack these clicks together"},{"time":232808,"text":"into buzzes and use them socially."},{"time":234943,"text":"For example, males will stimulate a female"},{"time":236921,"text":"during a courtship chase."},{"time":239425,"text":"You know, I've been buzzed in the water."},{"time":241752,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":243684,"text":"Don't tell anyone. It's a secret."},{"time":246065,"text":"And you can really feel the sound. That was my point with that."},{"time":248361,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":252093,"text":"So dolphins are also political animals,"},{"time":254618,"text":"so they have to resolve conflicts."},{"time":256929,"text":"(Dolphin noises)"},{"time":258572,"text":"And they use these burst-pulsed sounds as well as"},{"time":260945,"text":"their head-to-head behaviors when they're fighting."},{"time":263353,"text":"And these are very unstudied sounds"},{"time":265425,"text":"because they're hard to measure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267563,"text":"Now this is some video of a typical dolphin fight."},{"time":270282,"text":"(Dolphin noises)"},{"time":272303,"text":"So you're going to see two groups,"},{"time":274393,"text":"and you're going to see the head-to-head posturing,"},{"time":276601,"text":"some open mouths,"},{"time":279945,"text":"lots of squawking."},{"time":282101,"text":"There's a bubble."},{"time":285686,"text":"And basically, one of these groups will kind of back off"},{"time":288269,"text":"and everything will resolve fine,"},{"time":289923,"text":"and it doesn't really escalate into violence too much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293583,"text":"Now, in the Bahamas, we also have resident bottlenose"},{"time":295887,"text":"that interact socially with the spotted dolphins."},{"time":298831,"text":"For example, they babysit each other's calves."},{"time":301542,"text":"The males have dominance displays that they use"},{"time":303719,"text":"when they're chasing each other's females."},{"time":306119,"text":"And the two species actually form temporary alliances"},{"time":308541,"text":"when they're chasing sharks away."},{"time":310919,"text":"And one of the mechanisms they use to communicate"},{"time":313830,"text":"their coordination is synchrony."},{"time":315830,"text":"They synchronize their sounds and their body postures"},{"time":318941,"text":"to look bigger and sound stronger."},{"time":321075,"text":"(Dolphins noises)"},{"time":322551,"text":"Now, these are bottlenose dolphins,"},{"time":325143,"text":"and you'll see them starting to synchronize"},{"time":326914,"text":"their behavior and their sounds."},{"time":328815,"text":"(Dolphin noises)"},{"time":333183,"text":"You see, they're synchronizing with their partner"},{"time":335429,"text":"as well as the other dyad."},{"time":339401,"text":"I wish I was that coordinated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344731,"text":"Now, it's important to remember that you're only hearing"},{"time":347805,"text":"the human-audible parts of dolphin sounds,"},{"time":349700,"text":"and dolphins make ultrasonic sounds,"},{"time":351863,"text":"and we use special equipment in the water"},{"time":353421,"text":"to collect these sounds."},{"time":355158,"text":"Now, researchers have actually measured whistle complexity"},{"time":357723,"text":"using information theory,"},{"time":359786,"text":"and whistles rate very high relative to even human languages."},{"time":363677,"text":"But burst-pulsed sounds is a bit of a mystery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367529,"text":"Now, these are three spectragrams."},{"time":370616,"text":"Two are human words, and one is a dolphin vocalizing."},{"time":373291,"text":"So just take a guess in your mind which one is the dolphin."},{"time":379150,"text":"Now, it turns out burst-pulsed sounds actually look"},{"time":381743,"text":"a bit like human phonemes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384247,"text":"Now, one way to crack the code"},{"time":385513,"text":"is to interpret these signals and figure out what they mean,"},{"time":388058,"text":"but it's a difficult job, and we actually don't have a Rosetta Stone yet."},{"time":392056,"text":"But a second way to crack the code"},{"time":394178,"text":"is to develop some technology,"},{"time":396143,"text":"an interface to do two-way communication,"},{"time":398323,"text":"and that's what we've been trying to do in the Bahamas"},{"time":400687,"text":"and in real time."},{"time":403127,"text":"Now, scientists have used keyboard interfaces"},{"time":405783,"text":"to try to bridge the gap with species"},{"time":407847,"text":"including chimpanzees and dolphins."},{"time":409935,"text":"This underwater keyboard in Orlando, Florida,"},{"time":412960,"text":"at the Epcot Center, was actually"},{"time":414702,"text":"the most sophisticated ever two-way interface designed"},{"time":417519,"text":"for humans and dolphins to work together under the water"},{"time":420383,"text":"and exchange information."},{"time":422310,"text":"So we wanted to develop an interface like this"},{"time":424930,"text":"in the Bahamas, but in a more natural setting."},{"time":427300,"text":"And one of the reasons we thought we could do this"},{"time":429467,"text":"is because the dolphins were starting to show us"},{"time":431489,"text":"a lot of mutual curiosity."},{"time":433093,"text":"They were spontaneously mimicking our vocalizations"},{"time":436004,"text":"and our postures, and they were also inviting us"},{"time":438324,"text":"into dolphin games."},{"time":440957,"text":"Now, dolphins are social mammals, so they love to play,"},{"time":443604,"text":"and one of their favorite games is to drag seaweed,"},{"time":446924,"text":"or sargassum in this case, around."},{"time":450036,"text":"And they're very adept. They like to drag it"},{"time":452172,"text":"and drop it from appendage to appendage."},{"time":456492,"text":"Now in this footage, the adult is Caroh."},{"time":459188,"text":"She's 25 years old here, and this is her newborn, Cobalt,"},{"time":463060,"text":"and he's just learning how to play this game."},{"time":465744,"text":"(Dolphin noises)"},{"time":467470,"text":"She's kind of teasing him and taunting him."},{"time":471940,"text":"He really wants that sargassum."},{"time":476369,"text":"Now, when dolphins solicit humans for this game,"},{"time":479280,"text":"they'll often sink vertically in the water,"},{"time":482331,"text":"and they'll have a little sargassum on their flipper,"},{"time":484760,"text":"and they'll sort of nudge it and drop it sometimes"},{"time":487379,"text":"on the bottom and let us go get it,"},{"time":488913,"text":"and then we'll have a little seaweed keep away game."},{"time":491129,"text":"But when we don't dive down and get it,"},{"time":492965,"text":"they'll bring it to the surface"},{"time":494938,"text":"and they'll sort of wave it in front of us on their tail"},{"time":498112,"text":"and drop it for us like they do their calves,"},{"time":500198,"text":"and then we'll pick it up and have a game."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502400,"text":"And so we started thinking, well, wouldn't it be neat"},{"time":504750,"text":"to build some technology that would allow the dolphins"},{"time":507568,"text":"to request these things in real time, their favorite toys?"},{"time":510843,"text":"So the original vision was to have a keyboard"},{"time":513213,"text":"hanging from the boat attached to a computer,"},{"time":515386,"text":"and the divers and dolphins would activate the keys"},{"time":517901,"text":"on the keypad and happily exchange information"},{"time":520791,"text":"and request toys from each other."},{"time":522949,"text":"But we quickly found out that dolphins simply"},{"time":524743,"text":"were not going to hang around the boat using a keyboard."},{"time":527869,"text":"They've got better things to do in the wild."},{"time":530005,"text":"They might do it in captivity, but in the wild --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":532269,"text":"So we built a portable keyboard that we could push through the water,"},{"time":534994,"text":"and we labeled four objects they like to play with,"},{"time":537734,"text":"the scarf, rope, sargassum, and also had a bow ride,"},{"time":540675,"text":"which is a fun activity for a dolphin. (Whistle)"},{"time":542786,"text":"And that's the scarf whistle,"},{"time":544629,"text":"which is also associated with a visual symbol."},{"time":547547,"text":"And these are artificially created whistles."},{"time":549841,"text":"They're outside the dolphin's normal repertoire,"},{"time":552469,"text":"but they're easily mimicked by the dolphins."},{"time":554889,"text":"And I spent four years with my colleagues Adam Pack and Fabienne Delfour,"},{"time":559068,"text":"working out in the field with this keyboard"},{"time":561289,"text":"using it with each other to do requests for toys"},{"time":563933,"text":"while the dolphins were watching."},{"time":565592,"text":"And the dolphins could get in on the game."},{"time":566959,"text":"They could point at the visual object,"},{"time":568894,"text":"or they could mimic the whistle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571368,"text":"Now this is video of a session."},{"time":574736,"text":"The diver here has a rope toy,"},{"time":576937,"text":"and I'm on the keyboard on the left,"},{"time":579185,"text":"and I've just played the rope key,"},{"time":581833,"text":"and that's the request for the toy from the human."},{"time":585044,"text":"So I've got the rope, I'm diving down,"},{"time":588247,"text":"and I'm basically trying to get the dolphin's attention,"},{"time":590881,"text":"because they're kind of like little kids."},{"time":591949,"text":"You have to keep their attention."},{"time":594506,"text":"I'm going to drop the rope, see if they come over."},{"time":599193,"text":"Here they come,"},{"time":601697,"text":"and then they're going to pick up the rope"},{"time":603006,"text":"and drag it around as a toy."},{"time":604612,"text":"Now, I'm at the keyboard on the left,"},{"time":606397,"text":"and this is actually the first time that we tried this."},{"time":608707,"text":"I'm going to try to request this toy, the rope toy,"},{"time":611573,"text":"from the dolphins using the rope sound."},{"time":614141,"text":"Let's see if they might actually understand what that means."},{"time":619752,"text":"(Whistle)"},{"time":620978,"text":"That's the rope whistle."},{"time":623678,"text":"Up come the dolphins,"},{"time":624975,"text":"and drop off the rope, yay. Wow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628580,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":631564,"text":"So this is only once."},{"time":633324,"text":"We don't know for sure if they really understand the function of the whistles."},{"time":636132,"text":"Okay, so here's a second toy in the water."},{"time":638600,"text":"This is a scarf toy, and I'm trying to lead the dolphin"},{"time":640389,"text":"over to the keyboard to show her"},{"time":642726,"text":"the visual and the acoustic signal."},{"time":645916,"text":"Now this dolphin, we call her \"the scarf thief,\""},{"time":648983,"text":"because over the years she's absconded"},{"time":652476,"text":"with about 12 scarves."},{"time":655054,"text":"In fact, we think she has a boutique somewhere in the Bahamas."},{"time":658828,"text":"So I'm reaching over. She's got the scarf on her right side."},{"time":662522,"text":"And we try to not touch the animals too much,"},{"time":664286,"text":"we really don't want to over-habituate them."},{"time":666422,"text":"And I'm trying to lead her back to the keyboard."},{"time":668537,"text":"And the diver there is going to activate the scarf sound"},{"time":672483,"text":"to request the scarf."},{"time":674294,"text":"So I try to give her the scarf."},{"time":677043,"text":"Whoop. Almost lost it."},{"time":680018,"text":"But this is the moment where everything becomes possible."},{"time":682934,"text":"The dolphin's at the keyboard."},{"time":684679,"text":"You've got full attention."},{"time":686237,"text":"And this sometimes went on for hours."},{"time":688493,"text":"And I wanted to share this video with you"},{"time":689948,"text":"not to show you any big breakthroughs,"},{"time":691733,"text":"because they haven't happened yet,"},{"time":692853,"text":"but to show you the level of intention and focus"},{"time":695479,"text":"that these dolphins have, and interest in the system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698126,"text":"And because of this, we really decided we needed"},{"time":700147,"text":"some more sophisticated technology."},{"time":702241,"text":"So we joined forces with Georgia Tech,"},{"time":704441,"text":"with Thad Starner's wearable computing group,"},{"time":707117,"text":"to build us an underwater wearable computer"},{"time":709079,"text":"that we're calling CHAT. [CHAT: Cetacean Hearing And Telemetry]"},{"time":710945,"text":"Now, instead of pushing a keyboard through the water,"},{"time":712981,"text":"the diver's wearing the complete system, and it's acoustic only,"},{"time":716599,"text":"so basically the diver activates the sounds on a keypad"},{"time":719607,"text":"on the forearm,"},{"time":720786,"text":"the sounds go out through an underwater speaker,"},{"time":722974,"text":"if a dolphin mimics the whistle"},{"time":724384,"text":"or a human plays the whistle, the sounds come in"},{"time":726893,"text":"and are localized by two hydrophones."},{"time":729469,"text":"The computer can localize who requested the toy"},{"time":732816,"text":"if there's a word match."},{"time":734853,"text":"And the real power of the system is in the real-time"},{"time":737417,"text":"sound recognition, so we can respond to the dolphins"},{"time":739334,"text":"quickly and accurately."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741461,"text":"And we're at prototype stage, but this is how we hope it will play out."},{"time":745645,"text":"So Diver A and Diver B both have a wearable computer"},{"time":748923,"text":"and the dolphin hears the whistle as a whistle,"},{"time":751517,"text":"the diver hears the whistle as a whistle in the water,"},{"time":753997,"text":"but also as a word through bone conduction."},{"time":756429,"text":"So Diver A plays the scarf whistle"},{"time":758678,"text":"or Diver B plays the sargassum whistle"},{"time":760574,"text":"to request a toy from whoever has it."},{"time":762990,"text":"What we hope will happen is that the dolphin mimics the whistle,"},{"time":766199,"text":"and if Diver A has the sargassum, if that's the sound"},{"time":769369,"text":"that was played and requested,"},{"time":772114,"text":"then the diver will give the sargassum to the requesting dolphin"},{"time":775962,"text":"and they'll swim away happily into the sunset"},{"time":777778,"text":"playing sargassum for forever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":780895,"text":"Now, how far can this kind of communication go?"},{"time":784275,"text":"Well, CHAT is designed specifically to empower the dolphins"},{"time":788164,"text":"to request things from us."},{"time":789746,"text":"It's designed to really be two-way."},{"time":792139,"text":"Now, will they learn to mimic the whistles functionally?"},{"time":795418,"text":"We hope so and we think so."},{"time":797299,"text":"But as we decode their natural sounds,"},{"time":799443,"text":"we're also planning to put those back into the computerized system."},{"time":803031,"text":"For example, right now we can put their own signature whistles"},{"time":806531,"text":"in the computer and request to interact with a specific dolphin."},{"time":810626,"text":"Likewise, we can create our own whistles,"},{"time":814356,"text":"our own whistle names, and let the dolphins"},{"time":816675,"text":"request specific divers to interact with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819443,"text":"Now it may be that all our mobile technology"},{"time":822364,"text":"will actually be the same technology that helps us"},{"time":825500,"text":"communicate with another species down the road."},{"time":828731,"text":"In the case of a dolphin, you know, it's a species that,"},{"time":832363,"text":"well, they're probably close to our intelligence in many ways"},{"time":835746,"text":"and we might not be able to admit that right now,"},{"time":838289,"text":"but they live in quite a different environment,"},{"time":840113,"text":"and you still have to bridge the gap with the sensory systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844613,"text":"I mean, imagine what it would be like"},{"time":846297,"text":"to really understand the mind"},{"time":847906,"text":"of another intelligent species on the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":851691,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853039,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}